{
  "stem": "14897.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I don't think I was ever as religious again as I was during those 20 days, praying constantly for our lives.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "There was no electricity, no gas, no water.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "People had to go to the river to bring some buckets of water.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And food was limited, but there was some.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And at the end of that-- but I also remember soldiers in the streets, passing through Warsaw and the wounded people.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Then at the end of the month, of course, Warsaw was occupied by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, at first they were Polish retreating, and then they were German soldiers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At the beginning, there were tremendous shortages immediately.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We never went back to our apartment, but I remember we were staying with an uncle and aunt of mine.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Their names were Hurwicz, Zina and Adek.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Z-I-N-A and A-D-E-K H-U-R-W-I-C-Z.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the, the grownups had decided-- even though the violence at the beginning was sporadic and sort of random, there was not yet a concerted effort against Jews.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Of course, we knew already from the wars-- the years before the war what the German attitude was towards Jews.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, you know, before the war, what the Germans did with the Jews was they killed some, but they exiled many.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so there were refugees.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I remember that one of my girlfriend's, her parents took in a refugee family from Germany.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that we knew that the Germans-- we'd read in newspapers and so on-- it was known.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Although the Final Solution was not envisaged.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It could not be imagined by anybody, Hitler's Final Solution for the Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we did know.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
